cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a method for inferring and executing 3D shape programs using neural modules, which involves both computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves learning and self-supervised training, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with geometric structures and symbolic program structures, which could fall under cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The use of neural modules and self-supervised learning also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for program execution, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
